The paper deals with the problem of multi-view 3D reconstruction from images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves a new neural module and training algorithm, which are likely to fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of the proposed method for robotics applications, which could place it under the category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper involves the aggregation of deep features, which could potentially fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR).
